main event: A UFO sighting was recorded on September 7, 1956, in Henderson Harbor, New York, involving one circular shaped object.
interesting points: The object had a red interior and a green exterior., The object was detected on ground-radar moving laterally at approximately 45 mph., The sighting lasted for about 45 minutes before the object disappeared., The object was initially evaluated to be possibly caused by another aerial object rather than a balloon., Visual contact suggested the object might have been a star despite its unusual movement.
witness description: Members of the 655th AC&W Squadron and a student from Miss Syracuse College, all considered reliable.
